<Author>Papa Shep
<Content>Aussie Aussie Aussie Oi, Oi , Oi - Great location My wife, our 12 year old son and I checked in at the New York Helmsley on 17 January 2006 and checked out on 23 January 2006. 6 nights in total in New York for our holiday.We had booked through an internet site and didn't know what to expect. I emailed the hotel a few weeks before our visit to confirm that they had received our reservation. It did take the hotel 3 emails before they responded with a reservation number but it was still a week before our arrival. I did request a non smoking room on a high level and was advised they would do there best.We flew United airlines from Australia and our flight was expected to arrive at Newark at 8.00 p.m. on 17 January. All the United planes we flew on had mechanical problems resulting in us arriving in San Francisco 4 hours behind our connecting flight. United wanted to reschedule our flight to 10.30p.m San Francisco time meaning we would not arrive in New York until at least 7.00a.m. the next day. We kicked up and were seated on an earlier flight arriving at JFK just after midnight. We then arrived at our hotel around 1.30 a.m. in the morning and were greeted pleasantly by the front desk staff. We were told our room was on the 9th floor as they were booked out however we could pay US$50 per night for an upgrade. We declined. The gentleman who took our bags to our room was very friendly and we enjoyed our room. It was not an overly large room but was more than adequate for our needs. The bathroom was a very good size. The bed and the pillows were a bit soft for our liking and coming from the other side of the world our body clocks were all over the place. We had difficulty sleeping because of our excitement being in New York!We could hear the garbage collection going on during the night but it wasn't load and we got used to it.Our window was facing the office building next door so we didn't have a good view of the city as we had hoped.I was disappointed that our room did not have a fridge or a safe.The front desk has safety boxes for valuables that we used and this was pretty easy to use.When we left the hotel the next day we could see how close we were to everything!Grand Central 5 minute walk.United Nations 10 minute walkCentral Park 30 minute walkEmpire State Building 15 minute walkTimes Square 15 minute walkDowntown 5 minute walk 10 minute subway trainQuality affordable restaurants breakfast and dinner5 minutesEverything is close by and New York is a safe comfortable city to walk around.We did have breakfast in the restaurant one morning. The food was nice but the waiters were a bit stuck up and not all that friendly.The hotel security people were very discrete and friendly in their manner as was most staff at the hotel.There were a lot of airline staff and diplomats staying there.One difficulty staying on the 9th floor occurred every morning if you wanted to use the elevators. As people from higher floors were checking out the elevators rarely stopped on the lower floors for pick ups. We ended up walking down the stairs on one occasion. The stairs led us to the executive鈥檚 office and there was no clear signage to make it back to the lobby. We had a bit of fun with this as staff saw us walking around the executive office area and asked if they could help us. We told them thank you as the CEO has approved all their pay rise requests.Overall we paid AU$210 Australian dollars (about US$170) a night for the 3 of us to stay at the New York Helmsley.We felt we received value for our money as the hotel was clean and safe. The house keeping was very good replacing towels and toiletries each day.The room did get warm but when I opened a window it was very pleasant.The New York temperature for our stay was unusually mild (low-mid 50's) making it ideal for walking around this great city and returning to a comfortable clean room.As we had stayed at the Stanford Hotel on 32nd street last year, I would say that both hotels are equal except that the staff at the Helmsley is friendlier.We would recommend this hotel for people on holidays to stay because of its location and value for money high standards. 
